WEBVTT

00:01.096 --> 00:02.727
<i>MAN: Previously on</i> Almost Family...

00:02.727 --> 00:04.231
You have all your new sisters.

00:04.232 --> 00:05.373
That must be a plus.

00:05.374 --> 00:08.327
Yeah, except one is
dating a coworker of mine,

00:08.328 --> 00:10.370
<i>and the other one is sleeping
with a woman, which is great,</i>

00:10.371 --> 00:11.681
<i>except she's married to a man.</i>

00:11.682 --> 00:13.616
- Tim wants to have kids.
- So what do you want?

00:13.617 --> 00:14.684
I don't know what I want.

00:14.685 --> 00:15.709
<i>JULIA: I think that you two</i>

00:15.710 --> 00:17.117
<i>are very different people.</i>

00:17.118 --> 00:18.354
- Wow, you are jealous.
- I am not.

00:18.355 --> 00:19.597
Oh, ooh, so you're the gay one.

00:19.598 --> 00:21.214
Wait. [CHUCKLES] You're gay?

00:21.215 --> 00:23.149
- What the hell is wrong with you?
- Everything.

00:23.150 --> 00:25.194
I just wish you guys wouldn't
keep secrets from me.

00:25.195 --> 00:27.725
- You are seriously damaged.
- I'm sorry.

00:27.726 --> 00:29.181
I'm taking the subway. Good night.

00:29.182 --> 00:31.616
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

00:32.427 --> 00:35.946
<i>(MARK FONSECA'S "NEW DAY NEW START")</i>

00:35.947 --> 00:38.374
<i>FONSECA: ♪ I've got everything I need ♪</i>

00:38.375 --> 00:41.118
<i>♪ I've got everything I need ♪</i>

00:41.119 --> 00:44.696
<i>♪ I've got everything I need now ♪</i>

00:44.697 --> 00:46.239
Taxi.

00:46.240 --> 00:49.218
<i>FONSECA: ♪ Yeah, I've
got everything I need ♪</i>

00:49.219 --> 00:51.295
<i>♪ I've got everything I need ♪</i>

00:51.296 --> 00:52.862
I've always wanted to do that,

00:52.863 --> 00:54.382
hail a taxi in New York.

00:54.383 --> 00:56.208
Congratulations. Where to?

00:56.209 --> 00:57.727
West End Avenue.

00:57.728 --> 00:59.729
I'm going to see my father.

00:59.730 --> 01:03.232
<i>FONSECA: ♪ New day and a new start ♪</i>

01:03.233 --> 01:04.938
<i>♪♪</i>

01:04.938 --> 01:06.847
I still look like that, right?

01:06.848 --> 01:08.320
(PHONE CHIMES) _

01:09.797 --> 01:10.855
(PHONE BEEPS)

01:10.856 --> 01:12.765
Morning.

01:12.766 --> 01:14.284
The silent treatment. I deserve that.

01:14.285 --> 01:15.693
(CHUCKLES)

01:15.694 --> 01:17.812
Look, I...

01:17.813 --> 01:18.847
What I said about you,

01:18.848 --> 01:20.532
I didn't mean to hurt your feelings,

01:20.533 --> 01:23.201
and I clearly did, and I'm so sorry,

01:23.202 --> 01:26.629
and I got you some of those
yogurt drinks that you like.

01:37.165 --> 01:38.308
Oh, wow. Okay.

01:38.309 --> 01:39.433
(CHUCKLES)

01:40.812 --> 01:42.003
They're gross anyway.

01:42.004 --> 01:45.006
Rox, I'm so sorry.

01:45.007 --> 01:46.482
(PHONE CHIMES)

01:48.227 --> 01:49.602
These people will talk to me.

01:49.603 --> 01:50.821
<i>(UPBEAT MUSIC)</i>

01:50.822 --> 01:52.638
Don't you love the
city this time of year?

01:52.639 --> 01:54.807
Fall is so busy for me, though,

01:54.808 --> 01:56.609
but you gotta find time
for your personal life.

01:56.610 --> 01:57.702
Am I right?

01:57.703 --> 01:59.329
It beats unwinding with a glass of wine

01:59.330 --> 02:00.813
or a bottle of wine.

02:00.814 --> 02:01.906
A whole bottle.

02:01.907 --> 02:03.357
(LAUGHS) Am I right?

02:03.358 --> 02:04.817
It's just me alone,

02:04.818 --> 02:06.503
which is how I spend most of my time.

02:06.504 --> 02:08.338
Or at least that's how
I feel lately because

02:08.339 --> 02:11.416
everyone I know is... is mad at me.

02:11.417 --> 02:13.084
Dating apps? Like, who does these?

02:13.085 --> 02:14.177
Desperate. (LAUGHS)

02:14.178 --> 02:16.444
Is this a Blue Hawaiian? Aloha.

02:16.445 --> 02:17.827
(LAUGHS) Take me to the beach.

02:17.828 --> 02:20.041
You're, like, too good-looking.

02:20.042 --> 02:21.564
- (LAUGHS)
- It's making me uncomfortable.

02:21.565 --> 02:22.853
It's hot in here.

02:22.854 --> 02:25.504
But when I saw your picture,
I had to swipe right.

02:25.505 --> 02:27.724
Not left, right. Swipe right.

02:27.725 --> 02:30.101
Swipe right. Swipe right.

02:30.102 --> 02:33.029
(GULPING)

02:33.030 --> 02:34.698
Swipe right.

02:34.699 --> 02:38.075
This testimony from
Roxy's mom is so brutal.

02:38.076 --> 02:39.870
No matter how many times I read it...

02:39.871 --> 02:41.328
(SIGHS)

02:43.875 --> 02:45.783
Do you realize we haven't figured out

02:45.784 --> 02:47.960
which train we're taking to D.C.?

02:49.529 --> 02:52.624
For my grandmother's
80th birthday party.

02:52.625 --> 02:55.460
I forgot. I'm so sorry.

02:55.461 --> 02:57.411
If you're nervous, don't be,

02:57.412 --> 02:59.797
because I told everyone, "No baby talk".

02:59.798 --> 03:00.923
No, it's not that.

03:00.924 --> 03:03.622
It's just that is it really smart for us

03:03.623 --> 03:05.196
to both be out of the office

03:05.197 --> 03:07.731
after Amanda just
handed our asses to us?

03:07.732 --> 03:10.758
That's nothing compared
to what my mother will do

03:10.759 --> 03:12.843
if we miss Nana's 80th birthday party.

03:12.844 --> 03:13.928
You're right.

03:13.929 --> 03:16.055
I don't wanna mess with your mom.

03:16.056 --> 03:17.390
Right?

03:17.391 --> 03:18.483
I'm scared.

03:18.484 --> 03:21.394
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

03:21.395 --> 03:24.080
<i>♪♪</i>

03:24.081 --> 03:27.751
All right, well... (CLEARS THROAT)

03:27.752 --> 03:30.676
I guess there's a world where I can go

03:30.677 --> 03:33.256
all the way there by myself.

03:33.257 --> 03:35.783
If it wouldn't be too much trouble.

03:35.784 --> 03:37.880
When you're ready to sing
"Happy Birthday", call me.

03:37.881 --> 03:39.003
I'll sing along.

03:39.004 --> 03:41.022
It'll be great. It'll
be just like I'm there.

03:41.023 --> 03:42.098
Just like you're there.

03:42.099 --> 03:43.767
Yeah.

03:43.768 --> 03:45.960
<i>WOMAN: ♪ Caught me,
watch you work it, baby ♪</i>

03:45.961 --> 03:48.921
ROXY: Welcome to Round
Offs. Breathe it in.

03:48.922 --> 03:51.799
You smell that? That
is the smell of victory.

03:51.800 --> 03:54.110
<i>WOMAN: ♪ Put me in the right place ♪</i>

03:54.111 --> 03:55.400
IZZY: Did you really train here?

03:55.401 --> 03:57.528
ROXY: Yeah, I did, and you will too.

03:57.529 --> 04:00.959
Remember, you're only ever
in competition with yourself.

04:00.960 --> 04:02.935
NINA: Roxy? (LAUGHS)

04:02.936 --> 04:04.937
Roxy Doyle?

04:04.938 --> 04:06.647
ROXY: Nina Bennett.

04:06.648 --> 04:08.441
Wow, it's been a long time.

04:08.442 --> 04:09.803
What are you doing here?

04:09.804 --> 04:12.653
Just signing up my little
grasshopper for tryouts.

04:12.654 --> 04:14.004
- You?
- Uh, yeah.

04:14.005 --> 04:15.079
Same.

04:15.080 --> 04:17.709
Oh, what a coincidence.

04:17.709 --> 04:19.034
You know, truth be told,

04:19.035 --> 04:20.243
we almost didn't sign up at all.

04:20.244 --> 04:22.604
I mean, we weren't even sure
we were gonna need this program

04:22.605 --> 04:24.957
after our big win at
Montclair Classic last week.

04:24.958 --> 04:26.476
Oh, Montclair.

04:26.477 --> 04:27.793
Wow, you're still doing that?

04:27.794 --> 04:30.378
Well, we can't all
be like you, you know,

04:30.379 --> 04:32.816
in the big leagues,
shilling for energy drinks.

04:32.817 --> 04:34.559
Oh, that's right. They dropped you.

04:34.560 --> 04:36.319
- Mm.
- Ouch.

04:36.320 --> 04:38.471
Yeah, well, uh, we're really busy,

04:38.472 --> 04:39.990
but it was so good to see you.

04:39.991 --> 04:42.349
You too. Good luck.

04:42.350 --> 04:44.810
<i>♪♪</i>

04:44.811 --> 04:46.479
I really hope you stay healthy.

04:46.480 --> 04:49.690
<i>♪♪</i>

04:49.691 --> 04:51.835
Who was that?

04:51.836 --> 04:53.486
That was the enemy,

04:53.487 --> 04:55.839
and the enemy must be
destroyed at all cost.

04:55.840 --> 04:58.218
A minute ago you said I was
only in competition with myself.

04:58.219 --> 05:00.084
Yeah, well, our lives
were different then.

05:00.085 --> 05:01.511
Now it's game on.

05:01.512 --> 05:03.588
Let's get to work.

05:03.589 --> 05:07.183
<i>SINGER: ♪ Whoa, ooh-ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh ♪</i>

05:07.184 --> 05:10.353
<i>♪ Whoa, ooh-ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh ♪</i>

05:10.354 --> 05:11.503
Oh, good.

05:11.504 --> 05:13.672
Mrs. Peavy's coming in
at 3:00 for counseling.

05:13.673 --> 05:15.716
Uh, actually, it's for a referral.

05:15.717 --> 05:17.885
Uh, we found a surgeon who's confident

05:17.886 --> 05:19.771
he can resect her uterine septum.

05:19.772 --> 05:21.055
She didn't want surgery.

05:21.056 --> 05:22.723
She was considering other options,

05:22.724 --> 05:23.867
even surrogacy.

05:23.868 --> 05:24.976
What changed?

05:24.977 --> 05:26.651
I talked some sense into her.

05:26.652 --> 05:29.563
The procedure's hysteroscopic,
minimally invasive,

05:29.564 --> 05:31.357
takes an hour, tops.

05:31.358 --> 05:33.043
She saw the wisdom.

05:33.044 --> 05:34.527
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

05:34.528 --> 05:36.546
That's a professional ringtone.

05:36.547 --> 05:39.106
It's just a dating app. I
thought I had it on silent.

05:39.107 --> 05:40.599
You back on your dating app?

05:40.600 --> 05:42.785
The paint's not even dry from
the brother humper scandal.

05:42.786 --> 05:44.703
- That's brave.
- Oh, it's brave?

05:44.704 --> 05:46.056
- I'm just dating.
- No, I mean, you're right.

05:46.057 --> 05:48.224
It's... it's nothing
to be embarrassed about.

05:48.225 --> 05:49.516
Wait, now it's embarrassing?

05:51.211 --> 05:52.637
I don't know.

05:52.638 --> 05:55.139
Look, I am a modern
woman in New York City

05:55.140 --> 05:56.566
and, yes, I'm dating,

05:56.567 --> 05:58.050
but I'm dating judiciously,

05:58.051 --> 06:00.052
and don't put too much
pressure on Mrs. Peavy.

06:00.053 --> 06:01.737
It's her choice, not ours.

06:09.914 --> 06:12.131
Dr. Bechley?

06:12.132 --> 06:13.157
Can I help you?

06:13.158 --> 06:16.494
I'm Brian. Brian Madison.

06:16.495 --> 06:19.280
You treated my parents at your clinic.

06:19.281 --> 06:21.448
I found out that you're
my biological father.

06:21.449 --> 06:22.950
Oh?

06:22.951 --> 06:24.936
I took the train from
Des Moines to meet you

06:24.937 --> 06:26.412
and... and the whole way I imagined

06:26.413 --> 06:30.124
what this moment would be like.

06:30.125 --> 06:33.586
Well, uh, as you know,
there's a pending court case,

06:33.587 --> 06:35.462
so I have to limit my
interactions with...

06:35.463 --> 06:37.682
That's what you have to say?

06:37.683 --> 06:39.967
Some stupid legalese after
everything you've done?

06:39.968 --> 06:41.760
You don't just understand
my position and...

06:41.761 --> 06:43.621
My parents haven't stopped
fighting after they found out.

06:43.622 --> 06:46.031
- Very sorry to hear that, but...
- They're splitting up now.

06:46.032 --> 06:48.192
- Right.
- You broke my family.

06:48.193 --> 06:51.054
Well, okay, I made some
mistakes, uh, Brian.

06:51.055 --> 06:52.146
Many of them.

06:52.147 --> 06:54.607
Uh, I was always just trying to help.

06:54.608 --> 06:55.608
I... (BLOW LANDS)

06:55.609 --> 06:56.667
(GROANS)

07:02.690 --> 07:05.032
We should have a description
from the eyewitnesses soon,

07:05.033 --> 07:06.043
but in the meantime,

07:06.044 --> 07:07.637
we need two plainclothes officers

07:07.638 --> 07:09.330
in front of Dr. Bechley's building.

07:09.331 --> 07:10.956
- Yeah.
- Hey.

07:10.957 --> 07:13.309
What happened? Is he okay?

07:13.310 --> 07:16.503
Yeah. He's a little shaken up.

07:16.504 --> 07:18.389
Um, why is he not at a hospital?

07:18.390 --> 07:19.765
He was. He left.

07:19.766 --> 07:21.225
- They discharged him?
- No.

07:21.226 --> 07:23.060
He just left.

07:23.061 --> 07:24.061
Got it.

07:25.206 --> 07:29.285
Edie, I'm so sorry about what I did.

07:29.286 --> 07:30.851
Why don't you get in there and make sure

07:30.852 --> 07:33.854
Roxy isn't planning
any vigilante justice?

07:33.855 --> 07:36.332
I've got my hands full as it is.

07:36.333 --> 07:38.168
LEON: No, no, no, no.

07:38.169 --> 07:42.756
I don't want any trouble.
I mean it, Julia.

07:42.757 --> 07:44.281
- Are you okay?
- LEON: Yes.

07:44.282 --> 07:45.917
- Who did this?
- Oh, just one of my...

07:45.918 --> 07:47.808
It was a lunatic Bechley baby
who came all the way here

07:47.809 --> 07:49.241
from Iowa on a train.

07:49.242 --> 07:50.712
We have to find him and school him.

07:50.713 --> 07:52.089
Uh, no one's gonna school anyone.

07:52.090 --> 07:53.874
He was angry. He made his point.

07:53.875 --> 07:55.685
You know you should be at a hospital.

07:55.686 --> 07:58.712
No, they... they took my
X-rays. My vitals were fine.

07:58.713 --> 08:00.690
I just... I need a little rest.

08:00.691 --> 08:01.732
Thank you for being here.

08:04.436 --> 08:06.845
It's part of my job.

08:06.846 --> 08:08.197
But you're welcome.

08:11.869 --> 08:15.829
I'll go top off the apple.

08:19.192 --> 08:21.118
- When Edie told me...
- It's okay.

08:21.119 --> 08:22.437
I'm fine.

08:22.438 --> 08:24.455
You don't look okay. You
look like you got beat up.

08:24.456 --> 08:26.573
Were you scared? Should we be scared?

08:26.574 --> 08:29.410
No, he's the one who seemed scared.

08:29.411 --> 08:31.704
So how are things at the clinic?

08:31.705 --> 08:33.914
Dad, you know we're not
supposed to talk about work.

08:33.914 --> 08:35.390
Yeah, but I need the distraction.

08:36.467 --> 08:37.958
Fine.

08:37.960 --> 08:41.380
Um, well, we have an interesting
case right now, actually.

08:41.381 --> 08:42.457
A uterine septum.

08:42.457 --> 08:44.383
She's unsure if she wants to go forward.

08:44.384 --> 08:46.719
Obviously it's her choice
but what would you advise?

08:46.720 --> 08:48.312
Well, surgery, of course.

08:48.313 --> 08:51.241
It would be hysteroscopic,
minimally invasive,

08:51.242 --> 08:53.076
take an hour, tops.

08:53.077 --> 08:54.826
EDIE: Okay, great. Thanks.

08:56.321 --> 08:58.397
Roxy. Hey.

08:58.398 --> 08:59.991
Been meaning to ask you, uh,

08:59.992 --> 09:01.900
all that gay stuff that came out

09:01.901 --> 09:03.753
at the dinner from hell with Nate,

09:03.754 --> 09:05.570
could we just keep that between us?

09:08.408 --> 09:12.336
Edith, I would never
betray your confidence.

09:12.337 --> 09:14.246
You know, I have a lot of gay followers.

09:14.247 --> 09:16.064
I consider myself somewhat of an icon.

09:16.065 --> 09:17.267
No, I'm serious.

09:17.268 --> 09:19.677
My life is not for
your gymnastics groupies

09:19.678 --> 09:23.681
or your social needs or your friends.

09:23.682 --> 09:24.757
No one.

09:24.758 --> 09:28.093
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

09:28.094 --> 09:30.113
You and Julia are my friends.

09:30.114 --> 09:32.448
<i>♪♪</i>

09:32.449 --> 09:33.858
You're pretty much it.

09:33.859 --> 09:38.270
<i>♪♪</i>

09:38.271 --> 09:40.290
Okay.

09:40.291 --> 09:41.774
I'm glad you understand.

09:41.775 --> 09:45.444
<i>♪♪</i>

09:45.445 --> 09:47.279
Oh, okay.

09:47.280 --> 09:49.006
ROXY: That looks good. Point your toes.

09:51.951 --> 09:53.218
That girl's overextended.

09:53.219 --> 09:55.329
Her hip joints are gonna quit on her.

09:55.330 --> 09:58.382
She looks good to me, and
she's won competitions.

09:58.383 --> 09:59.583
IZZY: I can't beat her.

09:59.584 --> 10:02.669
Hey, don't ever say that again.

10:02.670 --> 10:04.338
Not only will you beat her,

10:04.339 --> 10:07.436
you will beat everyone who told
you you weren't good enough,

10:07.437 --> 10:08.801
including the voice in your own head.

10:08.802 --> 10:09.927
What did I tell you in the car?

10:09.928 --> 10:11.578
- 2028?
- 2028.

10:11.579 --> 10:12.897
That's right. Olympics are in LA.

10:12.898 --> 10:14.732
That's home turf.
You're taking the gold.

10:14.733 --> 10:16.326
Let me hear it.

10:16.327 --> 10:19.019
- I'm taking the gold.
- Why are you whispering?

10:19.020 --> 10:21.572
- Is it a secret?
- I... I'm taking the gold.

10:21.573 --> 10:24.858
- Louder!
- I'm taking the gold!

10:24.859 --> 10:27.653
(UPBEAT POP MUSIC PLAYING)

10:27.654 --> 10:29.413
♪♪

10:29.414 --> 10:30.797
Yes, we are.

10:34.536 --> 10:36.346
Edie Palmer for Amanda Doherty.

10:36.347 --> 10:38.497
LORENZO: The burden of
proof is on the state.

10:38.498 --> 10:41.151
I will show that the state
does not have evidence

10:41.152 --> 10:42.426
to convict my client.

10:42.427 --> 10:45.671
Furthermore, the harm caused
to my client by the state

10:45.672 --> 10:48.524
is unfair and damaging
to his reputation.

10:48.525 --> 10:49.842
Are you practicing

10:49.843 --> 10:51.602
for junior mock trial, by chance?

10:51.603 --> 10:53.270
Yeah. Have you done it before?

10:53.271 --> 10:55.681
I have, when I was about your age.

10:55.682 --> 10:56.866
LORENZO: Did you win?

10:56.867 --> 10:58.534
Well, it's not about who wins or loses.

10:58.535 --> 10:59.676
It's about learning.

10:59.677 --> 11:01.019
But if you must know, I crushed.

11:01.020 --> 11:03.614
That's cool.

11:03.615 --> 11:07.450
Use your client's real
name. It humanizes him.

11:10.738 --> 11:13.866
When you're defending
someone, you can't judge them.

11:13.867 --> 11:16.076
It's not your job.

11:16.077 --> 11:18.412
Slower. I'm writing this down.

11:18.413 --> 11:19.413
Oh, okay.

11:22.917 --> 11:25.018
LORENZO: Hey, Mom. You ready to go?

11:28.423 --> 11:29.882
(WHISPERING) This is your son?

11:29.883 --> 11:31.425
Yes.

11:31.426 --> 11:34.553
I see you've met Lorenzo.

11:34.554 --> 11:39.242
Enzo, baby, this is, uh...
this is Edie, Mom's friend.

11:39.243 --> 11:41.602
Now she's my friend, too,
because she's helping me

11:41.603 --> 11:43.821
win the mock trial. She
won when she was my age.

11:43.822 --> 11:45.230
AMANDA: Well, that's not surprising.

11:45.231 --> 11:47.107
Come to my house and after we practice

11:47.108 --> 11:48.951
I'll show you my owls, okay?

11:48.952 --> 11:51.278
Enzo, baby, go down
to the vending machine

11:51.279 --> 11:52.379
and I'll meet you there.

11:58.655 --> 11:59.946
What's going on here?

11:59.947 --> 12:02.432
I just came to drop off
our revised witness list.

12:02.433 --> 12:06.543
And your fancy firm doesn't
have messengers for that?

12:06.544 --> 12:08.846
I may have wanted an excuse.

12:08.847 --> 12:10.848
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

12:10.849 --> 12:13.019
Why didn't you tell me you have a son?

12:13.020 --> 12:14.610
I have an ex-wife, too, but, uh,

12:14.611 --> 12:18.281
that's all in a different
compartment, remember?

12:18.282 --> 12:20.691
I didn't mean to meet him,

12:20.692 --> 12:21.934
but now that I have,

12:21.935 --> 12:22.935
he's kind of a cool kid.

12:22.936 --> 12:25.121
<i>♪♪</i>

12:25.122 --> 12:27.820
He's been obsessing
over mock trial for weeks

12:27.821 --> 12:29.140
so if he needs your help,

12:29.141 --> 12:30.317
I guess you'll have to help him.

12:30.318 --> 12:31.997
No, we just met. He's
not gonna remember me.

12:31.998 --> 12:33.278
You don't know my son.

12:33.279 --> 12:35.363
He'll remember, and he'll pester me

12:35.364 --> 12:38.659
until the end of time, so...

12:38.660 --> 12:41.471
I guess I'll be seeing
plenty of you this weekend.

12:41.472 --> 12:45.472
<i>♪♪</i>

12:47.144 --> 12:48.552
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

12:48.553 --> 12:51.314
Hi. Oh.

12:51.315 --> 12:52.839
- Are you the nurse?
- Uh, no.

12:52.840 --> 12:55.726
I'm Roxy Doyle. And you are?

12:55.727 --> 12:58.069
Roxy, uh, she's a friend. Let her in.

12:59.823 --> 13:02.140
Edie told me. Are you all right?

13:02.141 --> 13:04.735
(LAUGHS) It wasn't that bad.

13:04.736 --> 13:07.020
Um, yeah, I'm sorry.

13:07.021 --> 13:08.313
Uh, I'm gonna need a name.

13:08.314 --> 13:10.241
Roxy, this is Genevieve.
She's Edie's mother.

13:10.242 --> 13:13.002
ROXY: Oh, you're an old friend.

13:13.003 --> 13:14.878
I didn't mean... um...

13:16.030 --> 13:17.172
How about I leave?

13:19.367 --> 13:20.826
- (DOOR CLOSES)
- She's feisty.

13:20.827 --> 13:22.494
(CHUCKLES) She had to be.

13:22.495 --> 13:25.560
So that was very kind
of Edie to, uh, call you,

13:25.561 --> 13:27.103
but seriously, I'm... I'm good.

13:27.104 --> 13:28.834
She isn't being kind.

13:28.835 --> 13:30.669
She's being your daughter.

13:30.670 --> 13:31.670
(CHUCKLES)

13:33.690 --> 13:39.011
- So I brought Doctor Coltrane.
- Hmm.

13:39.012 --> 13:40.229
Should I put him in the service?

13:40.230 --> 13:41.605
I have a better idea.

13:41.606 --> 13:44.298
Why don't we, uh, go to that
place we like in the Village?

13:44.299 --> 13:45.472
Hear something live?

13:45.473 --> 13:47.036
Should you be going out at all?

13:47.037 --> 13:49.955
No, but, uh, when have you
known me to follow orders?

13:52.066 --> 13:53.567
- ROXY: See that?
- Mm.

13:53.568 --> 13:56.028
Nina calls that a dismount?
That's garbage.

13:56.029 --> 13:57.701
Yeah, I can't really
tell because your screen

13:57.702 --> 13:58.714
is just a little cracked.

13:58.715 --> 14:01.612
Okay, the point is that if
that's what she's teaching

14:01.613 --> 14:03.553
her little Mini Me, then I got this.

14:03.554 --> 14:06.468
So you know Izzy's the
one competing, right?

14:06.469 --> 14:07.631
Not you?

14:07.632 --> 14:10.059
Okay, why don't we leave
the doctoring to you

14:10.060 --> 14:12.185
and the gymnastics to me?

14:18.643 --> 14:20.385
Whoa, uh...

14:20.386 --> 14:21.919
ROXY: Wow, relax, dude.

14:21.920 --> 14:23.546
It's just a little
on-top-of-the-clothes stuff.

14:23.547 --> 14:25.149
Okay, Isaac, you wanna tell me why these

14:25.150 --> 14:28.769
have my father's fresh
handwriting on them?

14:28.770 --> 14:32.230
Um, you brought home patient files.

14:32.231 --> 14:34.158
I saw him last night

14:34.159 --> 14:35.659
and he used your exact words

14:35.660 --> 14:37.253
about Mrs. Peavy's case.

14:37.254 --> 14:39.663
You've been working
with him behind my back.

14:39.664 --> 14:41.448
It wasn't "behind your back".

14:41.449 --> 14:43.259
JULIA: Then why not tell me about it?

14:43.260 --> 14:45.502
Probably because of this right here.

14:45.503 --> 14:46.893
ISAAC: I mean, I knew
you would overreact.

14:46.894 --> 14:48.339
Oh, asked and answered.

14:48.340 --> 14:50.266
JULIA: Do you know what would
happen if people found out

14:50.267 --> 14:51.842
that my dad is still handling cases?

14:51.843 --> 14:53.769
He just got attacked in the street.

14:53.770 --> 14:55.346
Do you want them to shut us down?

14:55.347 --> 14:57.297
What did you expect me
to do when you burned sage

14:57.298 --> 14:58.590
and installed hammocks?

14:58.591 --> 14:59.942
I'm a doctor.

14:59.943 --> 15:02.019
And I'm not one, so I have no value?

15:02.020 --> 15:03.657
Ooh, gotta give her that one.

15:03.658 --> 15:05.806
You know what? Go be a doctor.

15:05.807 --> 15:07.551
Go be a doctor somewhere else,

15:07.552 --> 15:08.601
because you're fired.

15:08.602 --> 15:09.643
- Whoa.
- Wait, no.

15:09.644 --> 15:10.884
- Wait, what?
- You can't... you can't fire me.

15:10.885 --> 15:12.437
I trusted you, Isaac,

15:12.438 --> 15:14.147
and because I can't trust you anymore,

15:14.148 --> 15:15.982
it's over.

15:15.983 --> 15:19.586
<i>♪♪</i>

15:24.617 --> 15:26.993
Hey, what the hell is your problem?

15:26.994 --> 15:29.472
You can't just fire Isaac
on some jealous power trip.

15:29.473 --> 15:32.716
I'm not jealous of you for dating Isaac.

15:32.717 --> 15:36.128
I meant jealous of
him for being a doctor

15:36.129 --> 15:37.462
when you never got your chance.

15:37.463 --> 15:39.297
Yeah, that's what I was saying.

15:39.298 --> 15:40.435
'Cause, you know, if
you're jealous of me...

15:40.436 --> 15:43.227
I'm not. I'm not.

15:43.228 --> 15:44.599
Is this why you've been suddenly

15:44.600 --> 15:46.525
- on the hookup hunt again?
- No, I'm not.

15:46.526 --> 15:48.157
(PHONE CHIMES)

15:48.158 --> 15:49.850
(PHONE CHIMING)

15:49.851 --> 15:51.351
Because, you know, if you're lonely,

15:51.352 --> 15:53.277
I can see if Isaac has
a friend or something,

15:53.278 --> 15:55.230
but, you know, you'd have
to hire him back first.

15:55.231 --> 15:56.253
(PHONE CHIMES)

15:56.254 --> 15:59.001
Okay, could you just
get out of my kitchen

15:59.002 --> 16:01.745
and out of my face right
now? I'm so sorry.

16:01.746 --> 16:02.929
- Please, that would be great.
- Mm.

16:02.930 --> 16:04.863
- If you could, like, go.
- Wow.

16:04.864 --> 16:07.200
It's a issue with the sound.
It's... I can't figure it out.

16:07.201 --> 16:08.785
It's... I don't know. (GROANS)

16:08.786 --> 16:09.860
Footsie, shut up!

16:09.861 --> 16:12.096
I don't need you anymore and
I'm deleting you right now,

16:12.097 --> 16:15.333
right after I just take one last look

16:15.334 --> 16:16.654
at who I would be missing out on.

16:19.356 --> 16:21.673
Did you know that there
are two kinds of owls?

16:21.674 --> 16:23.693
True owls and barn owls.

16:23.694 --> 16:25.861
Most of the time when people
think of an owl, though,

16:25.862 --> 16:27.029
they think of a true owl.

16:27.030 --> 16:28.864
EDIE: I am gonna remember that,

16:28.865 --> 16:31.841
and when anyone asks me,
I'll tell them you told me.

16:34.279 --> 16:35.729
All right, little man.

16:35.730 --> 16:37.337
It's time for bed. Go brush your teeth.

16:37.338 --> 16:39.691
LORENZO: Fine. See you soon, Edie.

16:39.692 --> 16:42.194
Good night. And remember,
when in doubt...

16:42.195 --> 16:44.696
- Object forcefully.
- That's right.

16:44.697 --> 16:47.049
Thank you for teaching
him that, by the way,

16:47.050 --> 16:49.367
'cause now he's gonna
object to everything I say.

16:49.368 --> 16:52.296
- Works for me in court.
- Mm, yeah.

16:52.297 --> 16:54.798
If you're defending the indefensible.

16:54.799 --> 16:57.042
Is that what you think?

16:57.043 --> 16:59.136
That what Leon did is indefensible?

16:59.137 --> 17:00.637
There's a case to be
made that there was...

17:00.638 --> 17:03.314
No, don't lawyer me.
What do you believe?

17:05.643 --> 17:08.528
I believe Diane's
testimony is compelling.

17:09.722 --> 17:11.906
And I believe that
people your dad affected

17:11.907 --> 17:14.076
have every right to be pissed.

17:14.077 --> 17:15.242
And you do too.

17:19.082 --> 17:21.250
I don't wanna talk about work anymore.

17:21.251 --> 17:22.666
I don't wanna talk at all.

17:27.448 --> 17:31.001
(CELL PHONE BUZZING)

17:31.002 --> 17:32.953
I... I'm sorry.

17:32.954 --> 17:36.122
Um, it's Tim.

17:36.123 --> 17:37.341
Okay, I gotta take it because

17:37.342 --> 17:38.989
it's his grandma's 80th birthday

17:38.990 --> 17:40.615
- and I promised I'd be available.
- It's fine.

17:40.616 --> 17:42.271
Lorenzo's probably
done brushing his teeth.

17:42.272 --> 17:43.668
- I should go tuck him in.
- Okay.

17:43.669 --> 17:46.633
It... it'll... just one second.

17:46.634 --> 17:48.301
- Hello? <i>
- TIM: Hey, it's time.</i>

17:48.302 --> 17:49.520
<i>What's going on with the video?</i>

17:49.521 --> 17:51.188
<i>- I can't see you.</i>
- EDIE: It's not working,

17:51.189 --> 17:52.222
but I can hear you.

17:52.223 --> 17:54.107
EDIE: Can you hear me?

17:54.108 --> 17:55.602
<i>TIM: Okay, I got her on speaker.</i>

17:55.603 --> 17:56.619
<i>You ready?</i>

17:56.620 --> 17:57.620
Yep.

17:59.289 --> 18:03.441
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

18:03.442 --> 18:06.085
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

18:08.322 --> 18:12.175
♪ Happy birthday dear Nana ♪

18:14.471 --> 18:17.263
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

18:18.833 --> 18:21.477
JULIA: So it's... it's
been kind of a rough week,

18:21.478 --> 18:23.627
and by rough week I mean a rough month.

18:23.628 --> 18:26.015
Sometimes I feel like that should
be the title of my memoir.

18:26.016 --> 18:28.300
<i>It's Been a Rough Month:
The Julia Bechley Story.</i>

18:28.301 --> 18:31.136
Uh, anyway, I... I work
in healthcare management.

18:31.137 --> 18:33.439
It's kinda the family business,
and now I run things.

18:33.440 --> 18:34.848
Well, trying to.

18:34.849 --> 18:38.327
Lately it's been one
setback after the next.

18:38.328 --> 18:40.486
Do you ever feel like that sometimes?

18:40.487 --> 18:42.147
Untethered professionally?

18:42.148 --> 18:44.316
I teach public school in
Union City, New Jersey,

18:44.317 --> 18:45.835
so yes.

18:45.836 --> 18:47.335
Right, English.

18:47.336 --> 18:48.486
Uh, what's that like?

18:48.487 --> 18:50.564
Forcing jockey football
players to read sonnets?

18:50.565 --> 18:52.174
- No bigger thrill.
- (CHUCKLES)

18:52.175 --> 18:54.200
It's cool to see a male English teacher.

18:54.201 --> 18:56.786
Studies show that girls
and women are more verbal.

18:56.787 --> 18:58.163
Really? I hadn't noticed.

18:58.164 --> 19:00.332
Right. (CHUCKLES)

19:00.333 --> 19:02.763
- You're so cute.
- Thank you.

19:02.764 --> 19:03.829
I didn't mean to talk about your looks.

19:03.830 --> 19:05.163
I heard that women feel condescended to

19:05.164 --> 19:06.555
when men compliment their looks.

19:06.556 --> 19:08.023
Who are these women? I
don't know these women.

19:08.024 --> 19:09.191
Should I condescend to you

19:09.192 --> 19:10.717
by saying you have mesmerizing eyes?

19:10.718 --> 19:12.603
- Yeah, I'm good with that.
- (CHUCKLES)

19:12.604 --> 19:15.388
Although, I... I can
offer you one thing.

19:15.389 --> 19:18.066
You don't quite come off
like you do in your profile.

19:18.067 --> 19:20.703
You're much less... cool.

19:20.704 --> 19:22.520
And not... that's not a bad thing.

19:22.521 --> 19:23.538
If you allow me...

19:24.899 --> 19:27.525
What, are you pulling
up my profile right now?

19:27.526 --> 19:29.527
(LAUGHS) Okay, this guy?

19:29.528 --> 19:32.214
This guy I expect to own a motorcycle.

19:32.215 --> 19:34.945
Wait, this picture's from
when I had my students

19:34.946 --> 19:37.410
read <i> The Outsiders</i> and
I dressed up as Dally Winston.

19:37.411 --> 19:39.463
(LAUGHS) Really?

19:39.464 --> 19:41.965
Oh, no, my son must
have gotten to my phone

19:41.966 --> 19:43.249
and changed my profile.

19:43.250 --> 19:44.468
I'm gonna kill him.

19:44.469 --> 19:45.905
Son? You have a... you have a son?

19:45.906 --> 19:47.379
- Yeah, Luke.
- Cool.

19:47.380 --> 19:49.214
He's 14,

19:49.215 --> 19:52.401
and his sister, Olivia, is 16.

19:52.402 --> 19:56.071
It's my first time on the app,
so Luke was particularly pushy.

19:56.072 --> 19:58.407
You have two teenage kids?

19:58.408 --> 19:59.849
Well, I guess it was
only a matter of time

19:59.850 --> 20:01.726
before I dated a divorced guy.

20:01.727 --> 20:03.285
Better divorced than married.

20:03.286 --> 20:04.413
Yeah, not divorced.

20:04.414 --> 20:06.582
Oh, I can't deal with
any more secret wives.

20:06.583 --> 20:08.066
Probably no. I already did that and...

20:08.067 --> 20:11.253
No, no, no, no, no, no.
My wife, uh, died

20:11.254 --> 20:13.113
a few years ago.

20:13.114 --> 20:15.925
Oh. I'm... I'm so sorry.

20:15.926 --> 20:18.333
We got married right after college,

20:18.334 --> 20:20.930
so I'm kinda rusty with
the whole dating thing,

20:20.931 --> 20:22.341
hence getting help from my kids.

20:22.342 --> 20:23.748
Right.

20:23.749 --> 20:25.676
Right, uh... (STAMMERING)

20:25.677 --> 20:27.319
If you will excuse me just for a moment,

20:27.320 --> 20:28.345
I'm gonna use the ladies room.

20:28.346 --> 20:29.846
Be right back.

20:29.847 --> 20:32.132
Sure.

20:32.133 --> 20:35.018
<i>(QUIRKY MUSIC)</i>

20:35.019 --> 20:36.928
<i>♪♪</i>

20:36.929 --> 20:39.597
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

20:39.598 --> 20:41.307
Come on. Come on.

20:41.308 --> 20:43.268
Go back in there. This is so rude.

20:43.269 --> 20:45.174
You're going back in there.
What is wrong with you?

20:45.175 --> 20:46.476
There's so much wrong with you.

20:46.477 --> 20:48.407
Go back in... you're
not going back in there.

20:53.946 --> 20:56.873
(JAZZY MUSIC PLAYING)

20:56.874 --> 20:59.802
LEON: The kid looked at me
with such desperate eyes.

20:59.803 --> 21:03.496
He wanted answers. I
couldn't give him anything.

21:03.497 --> 21:04.831
You know, I remember his case.

21:04.832 --> 21:07.643
His father had such a low
probability of conceiving.

21:07.644 --> 21:10.837
I truly wanted to help them,

21:10.838 --> 21:12.839
but, uh, you know, he didn't give me

21:12.840 --> 21:15.925
a chance to... say that.

21:15.926 --> 21:18.970
♪♪

21:18.971 --> 21:22.807
How much of all this
was you helping people

21:22.808 --> 21:24.184
and how much was you playing God?

21:24.185 --> 21:28.188
♪♪

21:28.189 --> 21:33.026
Boy, you sure know how to hold
my feet to the fire, don't you?

21:33.027 --> 21:35.170
- (CHUCKLES)
- Somebody's got to.

21:35.171 --> 21:37.655
♪♪

21:37.656 --> 21:40.591
(APPLAUSE)

21:43.346 --> 21:46.256
(BAND STARTS NEW SONG)

21:46.257 --> 21:48.017
♪♪

21:48.018 --> 21:49.667
And for our next song,

21:49.668 --> 21:51.854
I'm inviting a friend to join us.

21:51.855 --> 21:53.009
MAN: Leon Bechley.

21:53.010 --> 21:54.760
Leon, you still know this one?

21:54.761 --> 21:56.433
Yeah, no. Well, not tonight.

21:56.434 --> 21:58.676
Uh, you know, I'm just
catching up with an old friend.

21:58.677 --> 22:00.178
MAN: Tonight is the night, man. Come on.

22:00.179 --> 22:01.271
(CROWD WOOING)

22:01.272 --> 22:03.723
- Uh...
- Go on.

22:03.724 --> 22:06.184
(MUTTERS AND CHUCKLES)

22:06.185 --> 22:08.686
♪♪

22:08.687 --> 22:10.355
(SHARP WHISTLE)

22:10.356 --> 22:11.564
♪♪

22:11.565 --> 22:12.616
(GRUNTS)

22:12.617 --> 22:14.258
(CHUCKLES)

22:14.259 --> 22:15.329
♪♪

22:15.330 --> 22:17.168
MAN: Hey, is that the sperm guy?

22:17.169 --> 22:19.048
(LAUGHING)

22:19.049 --> 22:21.533
(RUMBLING)

22:21.534 --> 22:23.218
MAN: Doctor Switcheroo.

22:23.219 --> 22:24.961
(LAUGHING)

22:24.962 --> 22:27.222
MAN: Inseminate anyone
on the way over here?

22:27.223 --> 22:29.932
(HOLLOW ECHOING NOISE)

22:32.044 --> 22:34.712
MAN: Come on. What, are you leaving?

22:34.713 --> 22:37.215
I wanna hear the song.

22:37.216 --> 22:39.567
Aww, come on, man. Where are you going?

22:41.929 --> 22:43.888
I just wanted five minutes,

22:43.889 --> 22:46.224
just take my mind off of all of this.

22:46.225 --> 22:50.320
Well, I couldn't even get that.

22:50.321 --> 22:53.940
Forget about that jerk back there.

22:53.941 --> 22:56.459
Guy has a couple of scotches,
thinks he's a comedian.

22:58.254 --> 23:00.831
It's not just him. It's everyone.

23:00.832 --> 23:03.329
Young man who traveled
halfway across the country

23:03.330 --> 23:04.951
to attack me.

23:04.952 --> 23:06.886
You know, everyone's angry.

23:09.674 --> 23:12.267
Why weren't you?

23:12.268 --> 23:14.752
- Angry?
- Yeah.

23:14.753 --> 23:17.964
When you found out what I... what I did.

23:17.965 --> 23:20.851
I mean, you thought that
your donor was anonymous.

23:20.852 --> 23:22.110
Hmm.

23:23.446 --> 23:25.447
Because...

23:25.448 --> 23:29.526
there is so much to be
angry about in the world

23:29.527 --> 23:31.603
and I generally don't
waste my time being angry

23:31.604 --> 23:34.480
about things I can't change.

23:34.481 --> 23:39.169
And I was thankful to have Edie,

23:39.170 --> 23:40.486
any way I could.

23:40.487 --> 23:43.132
Yeah, well, people wanted children,

23:43.133 --> 23:45.208
and I made that happen, so on balance,

23:45.209 --> 23:47.343
didn't I do more good than harm?

23:53.667 --> 23:55.793
You're not a bad person,

23:55.794 --> 23:57.721
but you've done bad things.

23:57.722 --> 24:00.891
Things that have hurt people.

24:00.892 --> 24:05.228
Now, just because I'm
not the vengeful type

24:05.229 --> 24:07.972
doesn't mean I'm here to
make you feel better about it.

24:07.973 --> 24:11.142
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

24:11.143 --> 24:16.314
Maybe what you need to
feel right now is terrible.

24:16.315 --> 24:18.000
But you'll survive it.

24:18.001 --> 24:19.743
I promise.

24:19.744 --> 24:24.489
<i>♪♪</i>

24:24.490 --> 24:26.032
Nice.

24:26.033 --> 24:28.368
Somebody brought her A-game today.

24:28.369 --> 24:30.495
Podium's calling your name, girl.

24:30.496 --> 24:33.924
♪ Oh, my, oh, my, Oh, oh, my ♪

24:33.925 --> 24:35.425
♪ You start to tell me... ♪

24:35.426 --> 24:37.260
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

24:37.261 --> 24:38.670
(HEART BEATING)

24:38.671 --> 24:40.764
Roxy. Roxy Doyle.

24:40.765 --> 24:42.840
- How have you been?
- I've been good, Nick.

24:42.841 --> 24:45.551
- How you been?
- I'm never better.

24:45.552 --> 24:46.844
I see you're coaching now.

24:46.845 --> 24:48.271
Well, you know what they say,

24:48.272 --> 24:51.182
that children are our future.

24:51.183 --> 24:53.509
Izzy, this is Nick.
He used to coach here.

24:53.510 --> 24:55.520
So you're the reason
Roxy has all those medals?

24:55.521 --> 24:58.022
Um, I'm the reason I
have all those medals,

24:58.023 --> 24:59.708
and I will be the reason
you have all your medals.

24:59.709 --> 25:01.192
Go, practice.

25:01.193 --> 25:04.880
♪♪

25:04.881 --> 25:06.715
What are you doing here, Nick?

25:06.716 --> 25:08.383
Did Nina send you to remind us all

25:08.384 --> 25:10.410
what a boyfriend-stealing skank she is?

25:10.411 --> 25:14.223
Actually, I made an
offer to buy the gym.

25:14.224 --> 25:15.632
And they accepted it.

25:15.633 --> 25:18.400
Wow, I... I didn't know that.

25:18.401 --> 25:20.523
I'm more of a businessman
than a coach these days.

25:20.524 --> 25:21.897
Huh.

25:21.898 --> 25:25.091
Adding Round Offs to the
portfolio, though, is special.

25:25.092 --> 25:26.817
I made a lot of good memories here.

25:26.818 --> 25:27.843
Hmm.

25:27.844 --> 25:29.846
I'm glad that we could be
back in business together.

25:29.847 --> 25:32.148
♪♪

25:32.149 --> 25:34.409
We're not back in anything together.

25:34.410 --> 25:36.227
By the way, I'm happily married now.

25:36.228 --> 25:39.063
Nina and I ended it ages
ago, if you're wondering.

25:39.064 --> 25:40.415
I wasn't.

25:40.416 --> 25:42.734
Of course not.

25:42.735 --> 25:45.278
It was good to see you.

25:45.279 --> 25:47.589
I guess I'll be... I'll
be seeing more of you.

25:47.590 --> 25:48.665
Mm.

25:48.666 --> 25:50.366
♪♪

25:50.367 --> 25:52.669
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

25:52.670 --> 25:55.597
♪♪

25:55.598 --> 25:57.340
Izzy, let's go.

25:57.341 --> 25:59.009
Why? Is practice over?

25:59.010 --> 26:00.960
This is all over.
Practice... take this...

26:00.961 --> 26:02.795
tryouts, everything.

26:02.796 --> 26:03.892
I don't understand.

26:03.893 --> 26:06.275
♪♪

26:06.276 --> 26:09.969
It was a mistake to try out
for a gym team this soon.

26:09.970 --> 26:11.637
You're not ready.

26:11.638 --> 26:13.114
(KNOCKING)

26:16.619 --> 26:18.361
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

26:18.362 --> 26:21.606
Uh, is everything okay?

26:21.607 --> 26:23.107
- Is it my dad?
- No, it's me,

26:23.108 --> 26:25.627
and I am still mad at you,

26:25.628 --> 26:27.871
but I need advice on a messy situation

26:27.872 --> 26:30.114
and you are literally
the messiest person I know

26:30.115 --> 26:32.450
and I have no friends,

26:32.451 --> 26:34.636
so here I am.

26:34.637 --> 26:36.095
I am still seeing Amanda...

26:37.381 --> 26:39.424
And now it's super weird
because I accidentally

26:39.425 --> 26:41.334
met her son and he is obsessed with me

26:41.335 --> 26:42.719
and now I'm only getting in deeper

26:42.720 --> 26:44.146
and I have feelings for her,

26:44.147 --> 26:45.313
and I don't know what to do.

26:47.982 --> 26:49.746
Say something.

26:49.747 --> 26:51.197
I'm the messiest person you know?

26:51.198 --> 26:52.487
Julia!

26:52.488 --> 26:55.815
Well, obviously I'm not
thrilled that you're involved

26:55.816 --> 26:56.992
with my dad's prosecutor.

26:56.993 --> 26:59.182
Don't think of me as Leon's lawyer.

26:59.183 --> 27:00.812
Think of me as a sister.

27:00.813 --> 27:03.314
What would you tell...

27:03.315 --> 27:04.482
a sister?

27:04.483 --> 27:05.483
Um...

27:06.669 --> 27:09.670
I would tell her that I'm...

27:11.341 --> 27:14.918
I'm proud of her for taking a huge risk.

27:14.919 --> 27:16.635
For being so bold.

27:18.330 --> 27:21.350
But I would also tell her to be careful

27:21.351 --> 27:26.546
because I don't want to
see her or anyone get hurt.

27:26.547 --> 27:27.931
- (SIGHS)
- I know.

27:27.932 --> 27:29.674
My advice is very confusing. I'm sorry.

27:29.675 --> 27:31.509
No, it's okay.

27:31.510 --> 27:33.195
It's a confusing situation.

27:33.196 --> 27:36.106
I just don't want everything
to get screwed up,

27:36.107 --> 27:38.724
and I'm already in so deep.

27:38.725 --> 27:41.394
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

27:41.395 --> 27:42.445
(SNIFFLES)

27:42.446 --> 27:44.447
<i>♪♪</i>

27:44.448 --> 27:47.119
I'm sorry for calling you
the messiest person I know.

27:47.120 --> 27:48.734
No, it's accurate.

27:48.735 --> 27:51.737
I literally ran away from
a date that I had last night

27:51.738 --> 27:53.906
because he's an adult
human with children.

27:53.907 --> 27:56.367
Like, ran in heels.

27:56.368 --> 27:57.368
Not very far.

27:57.369 --> 27:58.445
Wow, okay.

27:58.446 --> 27:59.888
Um, I'm picturing that right now,

27:59.889 --> 28:03.359
and it looks, well, A, dangerous,

28:03.360 --> 28:05.376
B, insane. (SNIFFLES)

28:05.377 --> 28:08.212
<i>♪♪</i>

28:08.213 --> 28:10.473
Tell me that I can be bold,
too, before I chicken out.

28:10.474 --> 28:12.308
<i>♪♪</i>

28:12.309 --> 28:14.144
I mean, I don't know. It
kinda depends on what it is.

28:14.145 --> 28:15.478
(SIGHS)

28:15.479 --> 28:18.431
Go to New Jersey?

28:18.432 --> 28:20.892
Oh, wow, Julia.

28:20.893 --> 28:22.243
That is bold.

28:28.734 --> 28:31.420
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

28:31.421 --> 28:33.922
JULIA: Hey.

28:33.923 --> 28:37.116
Um, thanks for meeting me.

28:37.117 --> 28:39.428
Well, I'm mostly here to
collect the money you owe me

28:39.429 --> 28:40.453
from the other night.

28:40.454 --> 28:41.613
I made you an invoice.

28:41.614 --> 28:43.506
Oh, uh, yeah.

28:43.507 --> 28:45.675
I have some cash and I...

28:45.676 --> 28:46.768
- I'm joking.
- (CHUCKLES)

28:46.769 --> 28:48.294
Sort of.

28:48.295 --> 28:51.297
I can't tell you how sorry
I am about running out.

28:51.298 --> 28:54.943
That was weird and dramatic
and not really who I am.

28:54.944 --> 28:56.260
The one-two punch of teenage children

28:56.261 --> 28:57.861
and a dead wife was a lot to take.

28:57.862 --> 28:58.987
I know.

28:58.988 --> 29:01.357
Even a normal person would
struggle to get out from that.

29:01.358 --> 29:03.267
A normal person? Huh.

29:03.268 --> 29:05.120
I think I just got a little overwhelmed

29:05.121 --> 29:06.621
by the different places we're at.

29:06.622 --> 29:08.940
I mean, you have this full,

29:08.941 --> 29:11.400
rich life and a family, and I'm...

29:11.401 --> 29:12.869
Someone who runs away from restaurants.

29:12.870 --> 29:15.008
I was gonna say someone
who is just getting started.

29:15.009 --> 29:16.865
Late blooming is supposedly a thing

29:16.866 --> 29:18.019
with you millennials, right?

29:18.020 --> 29:19.617
You're a millenial too.

29:19.618 --> 29:22.171
I'm 38 so actually I'm an Xennial.

29:22.172 --> 29:23.220
Now you're just making up words.

29:23.221 --> 29:25.882
No, no, Xennials are between
generation X and millenials,

29:25.883 --> 29:27.217
born during Carter's presidency.

29:27.218 --> 29:28.626
- You can look it up.
- (LAUGHS)

29:28.627 --> 29:30.136
Are we really that different?

29:30.137 --> 29:32.313
No, in fact I was a
little intimidated by you.

29:32.314 --> 29:34.700
- (LAUGHS) You were?
- Yeah, the whole time that you were, like,

29:34.701 --> 29:37.159
blathering on and on
and on, I just thought,

29:37.160 --> 29:39.262
"I wish she saw herself the way
that other people must see her".

29:39.263 --> 29:40.563
Do I do that? I blather?

29:40.564 --> 29:42.065
Other than dining and dashing,

29:42.066 --> 29:44.183
it's your least redeeming quality.

29:44.184 --> 29:45.740
I talk a lot when I'm nervous

29:45.741 --> 29:47.459
and... and when I'm doing something new,

29:47.460 --> 29:50.523
and you were... and you
are something new for me.

29:50.524 --> 29:51.833
A grown-up.

29:51.834 --> 29:54.318
I didn't know if I was ready for that

29:54.319 --> 29:55.987
and it turns out I wasn't.

29:55.988 --> 29:57.605
So what do I owe you?

29:57.606 --> 29:59.508
I... like, 20? 40?

29:59.509 --> 30:01.158
- How expensive was that?
- You're asking?

30:01.159 --> 30:02.511
I literally made you an invoice.

30:02.512 --> 30:04.203
(LAUGHING)

30:04.204 --> 30:05.538
Listen, it was new for me too.

30:05.539 --> 30:07.422
Yeah, I guess it taught
me I'm a little old

30:07.423 --> 30:09.834
for the whole dating app
thing, so thank you for that.

30:09.835 --> 30:11.261
You're not old.

30:11.262 --> 30:12.837
You could still see the screen

30:12.838 --> 30:15.357
when your kids handed it to you.

30:15.358 --> 30:16.507
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

30:16.508 --> 30:18.911
- Sorry.
- Uh, I don't know.

30:18.912 --> 30:20.695
Old-fashioned, then, I guess.

30:20.696 --> 30:22.939
I still believe in, like,
all these outdated things,

30:22.940 --> 30:27.076
like romance and soul mates.

30:28.061 --> 30:30.730
Okay, you are 100 years old.

30:30.731 --> 30:33.035
(LAUGHS) No, you're
not 100. You're not old.

30:33.036 --> 30:35.568
I mean, you're maybe
100 if it was on a scale

30:35.569 --> 30:38.713
of, like, one to ten and
you're 100 'cause of hotness.

30:38.714 --> 30:40.573
(GROANS)

30:40.574 --> 30:43.034
Oh, God. Did I say that?

30:43.035 --> 30:44.627
I can't bel... you know, it's funny.

30:44.628 --> 30:46.081
I didn't think I could
make this any more awkward,

30:46.082 --> 30:47.297
and then I did.

30:47.298 --> 30:50.541
Anyway, uh, good luck

30:50.542 --> 30:52.003
with, you know,

30:52.004 --> 30:53.753
your whole online dating thing.

30:53.754 --> 30:55.972
You know, I hope you find what
you're looking for, seriously.

30:55.973 --> 30:58.066
You deserve it.

30:58.067 --> 30:59.753
Yeah, um...

30:59.754 --> 31:02.663
Do we, like, handshake or hug? Okay.

31:02.664 --> 31:03.980
- We can hug it out.
- Oh.

31:03.981 --> 31:05.240
- Thanks.
- Take care.

31:05.241 --> 31:08.059
Yeah, thanks. You... you too.

31:08.060 --> 31:09.652
<i>(UPBEAT MUSIC)</i>

31:09.653 --> 31:11.079
(SIGHS)

31:11.080 --> 31:12.938
EDIE: My investigators found him

31:12.939 --> 31:14.931
at a youth hostel by Port Authority.

31:14.932 --> 31:16.797
He could hop on a bus at any moment,

31:16.798 --> 31:18.609
so if you want to press charges,

31:18.610 --> 31:20.496
you should probably
do it before he leaves.

31:20.497 --> 31:23.074
I don't. He's suffered enough.

31:23.075 --> 31:24.633
Okay, well...

31:29.081 --> 31:31.841
(INHALES DEEPLY)

31:31.842 --> 31:33.793
Do I smell oil of oregano?

31:33.794 --> 31:35.419
W... why... why do you ask?

31:35.420 --> 31:37.680
(SNIFFS)

31:37.681 --> 31:38.881
Has my mother been here?

31:38.882 --> 31:41.109
(CHUCKLES)

31:41.110 --> 31:43.235
We're friends. Have been for many years.

31:45.263 --> 31:48.358
So you guys are... you
guys are, like, hanging out?

31:48.359 --> 31:50.434
I wouldn't call it that, per se.

31:50.435 --> 31:52.118
Well as your attorney,
I don't advise it.

31:52.119 --> 31:53.630
In case the prosecution gets to her,

31:53.631 --> 31:54.980
it could be seen as witness tampering

31:54.981 --> 31:56.349
and it could open up a
whole other can of worms...

31:56.350 --> 31:58.034
Edie, I appreciate
you looking out for me

31:58.035 --> 31:59.667
in that regard, but it's Sunday.

31:59.668 --> 32:01.946
Take the day off from being my lawyer

32:01.947 --> 32:04.040
and try being my daughter.

32:04.041 --> 32:06.209
LEON: Okay?

32:06.210 --> 32:09.553
I just want you to know that...

32:11.164 --> 32:12.807
I admire you.

32:12.808 --> 32:14.499
This case must be taking its toll,

32:14.500 --> 32:16.961
but I know that I'm in good hands.

32:16.962 --> 32:19.839
You're brilliant.

32:19.840 --> 32:20.965
Always have been.

32:20.966 --> 32:23.926
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

32:23.927 --> 32:26.345
<i>♪♪</i>

32:26.346 --> 32:27.656
Well, just let me know if you

32:27.657 --> 32:29.807
change your mind about pressing charges.

32:29.808 --> 32:30.975
Yeah.

32:30.976 --> 32:33.018
<i>♪♪</i>

32:33.019 --> 32:35.354
(SIGHS)

32:35.355 --> 32:36.795
Thank you very much, counselor.

32:38.525 --> 32:41.077
WOMAN: Prosecutor, your
witness for cross-examination.

32:41.078 --> 32:42.671
What time did you arrive home?

32:42.672 --> 32:44.339
10:00 p.m. sharp.

32:44.340 --> 32:47.583
So it wasn't 11:30? That's
what you said earlier.

32:47.584 --> 32:50.202
Objection. Asked and answered.

32:50.203 --> 32:51.846
WOMAN: Sustained.

32:51.847 --> 32:53.038
Move on, counselor.

32:53.039 --> 32:55.925
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

32:55.926 --> 32:57.927
<i>♪♪</i>

32:57.928 --> 32:59.971
GIRL: Going back to the timeline,

32:59.972 --> 33:04.277
you swore in your deposition
that when you got home,

33:04.278 --> 33:05.399
you saw the defendant.

33:05.400 --> 33:09.272
<i>♪♪</i>

33:09.273 --> 33:11.460
I know you've been working
with Isaac behind my back.

33:11.461 --> 33:12.701
LEON: Well, we're doctors

33:12.702 --> 33:14.389
and we have a duty to our patients.

33:15.204 --> 33:16.896
JULIA: Not anymore.

33:16.897 --> 33:19.190
I fired Isaac.

33:19.191 --> 33:20.799
Please tell me you didn't do that.

33:20.800 --> 33:22.359
I did. You can't undermine me.

33:22.360 --> 33:24.057
You can't fire Isaac.

33:24.058 --> 33:25.749
He is a superb physician.

33:25.750 --> 33:28.240
He is one of the finest
talents I've ever seen.

33:28.241 --> 33:29.867
Because he learned from the best.

33:29.868 --> 33:32.578
And he needs the job
to stay in the country.

33:32.579 --> 33:34.561
His visa situation's precarious,

33:34.562 --> 33:35.915
to say the least.

33:35.916 --> 33:39.009
Precarious? Like... like
deported, precarious?

33:39.010 --> 33:40.085
Yes.

33:40.086 --> 33:42.138
Why didn't either of
you two tell me that?

33:42.139 --> 33:44.214
All you do is keep things from me.

33:44.215 --> 33:45.925
To protect you.

33:45.926 --> 33:47.736
Then why put me in the bylaws?

33:47.737 --> 33:50.071
Why give me the clinic if
you don't even trust me?

33:50.072 --> 33:51.406
- I trust you.
- Then prove it.

33:51.407 --> 33:54.650
I'm your daughter. I'm the special one.

33:54.651 --> 33:57.061
No more meddling. No
more back-channeling.

33:57.062 --> 33:58.371
You have to let me run things my way.

33:58.372 --> 33:59.801
Julia, I love you, but don't ask me

33:59.802 --> 34:01.347
for the one thing I can't give you.

34:01.348 --> 34:02.457
I'm a doctor. It's who I am,

34:02.458 --> 34:03.943
so unless they lock me up forever,

34:03.944 --> 34:06.265
I am returning to the clinic
that I built from nothing.

34:06.266 --> 34:07.330
I built it too.

34:07.331 --> 34:09.039
Every baby picture on that wall,

34:09.040 --> 34:10.407
every video testimonial.

34:10.408 --> 34:12.576
I may not have a bunch
of letters after my name,

34:12.577 --> 34:14.929
but that clinic is just as
much mine as it is yours.

34:14.929 --> 34:16.956
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

34:16.956 --> 34:18.174
What's this really about?

34:18.175 --> 34:20.417
<i>♪♪</i>

34:20.418 --> 34:24.105
From now on, you have
to be honest with me.

34:24.106 --> 34:28.358
<i>♪♪</i>

34:31.933 --> 34:34.199
So I'm hiring back Isaac.

34:34.199 --> 34:37.786
It was too quick for me to
fire him in the first place.

34:37.786 --> 34:39.380
You listened to me.

34:39.382 --> 34:40.813
That really means a lot.

34:40.813 --> 34:43.284
Well, actually it was...

34:43.284 --> 34:45.293
Yes, I did. I listened to you.

34:45.293 --> 34:47.591
You know, I'm really happy I don't
have to scowl at you anymore,

34:47.592 --> 34:49.621
'cause I could really use
your help finding a new job.

34:49.623 --> 34:52.000
I was thinking I could teach
strength training at the clinic.

34:52.001 --> 34:53.042
JULIA: It's not a gym.

34:53.043 --> 34:54.636
Isaac said there's yoga.

34:54.637 --> 34:56.512
Aren't you already
working at your old gym?

34:57.881 --> 34:58.889
I can't.

35:00.551 --> 35:03.886
Going there day after
day just to have my past

35:03.887 --> 35:06.556
thrown in my face, it's a sewer fire.

35:06.557 --> 35:08.316
You mean dumpster fire.

35:08.317 --> 35:10.726
I'm being vulnerable and
you're correcting my slang?

35:10.727 --> 35:12.820
Who's throwing your past in your face?

35:14.398 --> 35:16.515
When I was competing,

35:16.516 --> 35:20.657
I had this frenemy, Nina Bennett.

35:20.658 --> 35:22.738
She one-upped me every chance she got.

35:22.739 --> 35:25.912
She even stole my old boyfriend
who now owns the place.

35:25.913 --> 35:28.643
But seeing them there
with their tight-lip grins,

35:28.644 --> 35:29.671
I just... I can't take it.

35:29.672 --> 35:31.247
I had to get out of there
and take Izzy with me.

35:31.248 --> 35:32.698
Okay, Roxy, down that mimosa

35:32.699 --> 35:34.548
because Julia and I
are gonna break it down.

35:34.549 --> 35:35.688
- Go on.
- JULIA: Mm-hmm.

35:35.689 --> 35:37.563
EDIE: First of all, you
pulled Izzy out of tryouts?

35:37.564 --> 35:38.598
JULIA: Just because you couldn't handle

35:38.599 --> 35:39.704
seeing an old teenage boyfriend?

35:39.705 --> 35:40.981
EDIE: That little girl
is counting on you.

35:40.982 --> 35:42.766
You filled her head with dreams.
You can't abandon her.

35:42.767 --> 35:44.161
And who is this Nina person, anyway?

35:44.162 --> 35:45.703
EDIE: Yeah. We don't know her.
We don't care to know her.

35:45.704 --> 35:47.597
Take it from me. Running
away is not the answer.

35:47.598 --> 35:49.847
You're Roxy Doyle. Floor
exercise bronze medalist.

35:49.848 --> 35:52.009
It was balance beam and silver.

35:52.010 --> 35:53.216
But I get your point.

35:53.217 --> 35:55.220
ROXY: Okay, I'm gonna text
Izzy to be ready in 20.

35:55.221 --> 35:57.106
Let's pound some water, sober up,

35:57.107 --> 35:58.274
and ruin some lives.

35:58.275 --> 35:59.892
(TIRES SQUEALING)

35:59.893 --> 36:01.035
(HORN HONKING)

36:01.036 --> 36:02.945
Izzy!

36:02.946 --> 36:05.281
<i>(UPBEAT MUSIC)</i>

36:05.282 --> 36:07.542
You don't need to get ready. Why?

36:07.543 --> 36:09.902
- Because we were born ready.
- That's right!

36:09.903 --> 36:12.738
<i>♪♪</i>

36:12.739 --> 36:14.790
<i>WOMAN: ♪ Take a little, take a lot ♪</i>

36:14.791 --> 36:17.793
<i>♪ There's nothing I ain't got ♪</i>

36:17.794 --> 36:21.556
<i>♪ I bet you never thought
that you could have it all ♪</i>

36:21.557 --> 36:24.208
<i>♪ It's here for you ♪</i>

36:24.209 --> 36:26.728
<i>♪ Get ready, break through ♪</i>

36:26.729 --> 36:28.062
<i>♪ Come and get it ♪</i>

36:28.063 --> 36:29.445
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

36:29.446 --> 36:31.807
- That one was not so good.
- Oh, what are you talking about?

36:31.808 --> 36:32.901
- It was perfect.
- It was great.

36:32.902 --> 36:34.385
Civilians.

36:34.386 --> 36:35.811
<i>WOMAN: ♪ You can have it all ♪</i>

36:35.812 --> 36:39.098
<i>♪ You can have everything ♪</i>

36:39.099 --> 36:40.241
<i>♪ Set your spirit free ♪</i>

36:40.242 --> 36:41.392
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

36:41.393 --> 36:43.769
Nice job. That was great.

36:43.770 --> 36:45.711
Okay, we really need to
work on your form, though.

36:45.712 --> 36:48.065
I am so proud of you. Don't forget.

36:48.066 --> 36:50.234
You are a legend.

36:50.235 --> 36:52.921
(POP MUSIC PLAYING QUIETLY)

36:52.922 --> 36:54.830
Do you think that's the ex?

36:54.831 --> 36:57.616
Yeah, she said he owns the place.

36:57.617 --> 36:59.822
Didn't she make it seem like
they were both teenagers?

36:59.823 --> 37:00.841
EDIE: Yeah.

37:00.842 --> 37:03.431
There's no way Roxy was
the same age as that guy.

37:03.432 --> 37:07.251
Izzy, congratulations.

37:07.252 --> 37:08.836
Welcome to the Round Offs team.

37:08.837 --> 37:10.119
- Seriously?
- NICK: Seriously.

37:10.120 --> 37:11.773
- Oh, my God!
- (BOTH GIGGLING)

37:11.774 --> 37:14.442
- Thank you, thank you, thank you!
- Oh, good job. Good job.

37:14.443 --> 37:15.944
- IZZY: Thank you!
- Go meet your team.

37:15.945 --> 37:19.571
♪♪

37:22.267 --> 37:23.267
Hi. Can I...

37:24.144 --> 37:25.144
ISAAC: Yeah. Come in.

37:27.614 --> 37:29.982
This isn't what I imagined
your apartment would look like.

37:29.983 --> 37:33.962
I pictured some slick
Wall Street bachelor pad.

37:33.963 --> 37:36.631
Well, sorry to disappoint.

37:36.632 --> 37:39.283
I, uh, send most of what I
make back home to my family.

37:39.284 --> 37:41.711
Goes further there than it does here.

37:41.712 --> 37:43.742
Why didn't you tell me
about your citizenship?

37:43.743 --> 37:46.331
It's nobody's business but mine.

37:46.332 --> 37:48.884
I obviously want you to stay here,

37:48.885 --> 37:50.794
but you betrayed me.

37:50.795 --> 37:52.188
I thought we were a team.

37:52.189 --> 37:53.961
So why were you so willing to fire me?

37:53.962 --> 37:55.315
Because I was upset.

37:58.562 --> 38:01.680
Did this have anything
to do with Roxy and me?

38:01.681 --> 38:04.308
Don't flatter yourself, okay?

38:04.309 --> 38:06.068
I need to be able to trust you.

38:06.069 --> 38:08.854
Your dad, as tough as he is,

38:08.855 --> 38:10.832
he made me into the doctor I am today.

38:10.833 --> 38:12.858
It's time to take the
training wheels off.

38:12.859 --> 38:15.336
Look, I know how hard that feels.

38:15.337 --> 38:17.413
Believe me.

38:17.414 --> 38:18.822
You're ready.

38:18.823 --> 38:20.657
Ah.

38:20.658 --> 38:22.493
So does that mean...

38:22.494 --> 38:24.703
The job is yours again

38:24.704 --> 38:26.848
if you still want it.

38:26.849 --> 38:29.666
Yeah, I'll, uh... I'll think about it.

38:29.667 --> 38:32.261
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

38:32.262 --> 38:33.763
- All right.
- Mm.

38:33.764 --> 38:35.097
Took you long enough. (CHUCKLES)

38:35.098 --> 38:36.173
(PHONE CHIMING)

38:36.174 --> 38:37.600
Oh, God. Oh, God!

38:37.601 --> 38:40.440
Ah, you're still, uh,
dating judiciously?

38:40.441 --> 38:42.237
I can't turn the sound off.

38:51.898 --> 38:54.024
Ah! It's for Lorenzo,

38:54.025 --> 38:56.118
for killing it at mock trial.

38:56.119 --> 38:58.237
Thank you.

38:58.238 --> 38:59.671
He'll love it.

39:06.079 --> 39:07.889
That's all?

39:07.890 --> 39:12.042
I know that you are living
this heavy-ass double life,

39:12.043 --> 39:14.303
and I'm sympathetic,

39:14.304 --> 39:18.399
but I can't keep doing this.

39:18.400 --> 39:21.069
I'm falling in love with you.

39:21.070 --> 39:23.525
I had a life I could manage,

39:23.526 --> 39:25.447
and then you came
along and... and you...

39:26.391 --> 39:28.317
You rearranged my molecules.

39:28.318 --> 39:30.452
You... and I...

39:31.563 --> 39:33.272
I can't go back.

39:33.273 --> 39:35.899
♪♪

39:35.900 --> 39:37.209
I...

39:38.778 --> 39:41.589
I can't go back, either.

39:41.590 --> 39:43.348
<i>♪♪</i>

39:43.349 --> 39:44.736
I'm falling in love with you too.

39:44.737 --> 39:47.452
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

39:47.453 --> 39:51.841
<i>WOMAN: ♪ And I throw it
all, throw it all away ♪</i>

39:51.842 --> 39:55.085
<i>♪ If you told me what to say ♪</i>

39:55.086 --> 39:58.681
<i>♪ Keep the demons far away ♪</i>

39:58.682 --> 40:00.775
What do we do now?

40:00.776 --> 40:02.818
<i>WOMAN: ♪ Throw it all away ♪</i>

40:05.188 --> 40:07.280
(PHONE CHIMING)

40:17.660 --> 40:19.484
_

40:19.485 --> 40:20.627
(LOW TONE)

40:31.214 --> 40:34.308
<i>(THE CURTAIN CALLS'
"HERE'S TO THE FUTURE")</i>

40:34.309 --> 40:38.309
<i>♪♪</i>

40:43.018 --> 40:47.396
<i>MAN: ♪ Take your time, there's no rush ♪</i>

40:47.397 --> 40:48.564
(LINE TRILLING)

40:48.565 --> 40:50.140
<i>♪ Do your best ♪</i>

40:50.141 --> 40:52.184
<i>MAN: Hello?</i>

40:52.185 --> 40:53.903
So I looked it up,

40:53.904 --> 40:57.147
and Xennials are apparently a thing.

40:57.148 --> 40:58.499
(LAUGHS)

40:58.500 --> 41:00.075
It sounds like you learned something.

41:00.076 --> 41:02.170
Unsurprising, since I'm a teacher.

41:02.171 --> 41:05.030
<i>MAN: ♪ Here's to the future ♪</i>

41:05.031 --> 41:07.532
I don't wanna run anymore.

41:07.533 --> 41:11.370
Not from people. Not you.

41:11.371 --> 41:12.680
So don't run.

41:12.681 --> 41:14.873
Walk, crawl, whatever,

41:14.874 --> 41:17.018
as long as it's in my direction.

41:17.019 --> 41:19.854
<i>MAN: ♪ And the lessons we learned ♪</i>

41:19.855 --> 41:21.931
<i>♪ Here's to our future ♪</i>

41:21.932 --> 41:24.099
I can't tell. Are you...

41:24.100 --> 41:27.177
I'm smiling. (CHUCKLES)

41:27.178 --> 41:28.553
I'm smiling.

41:28.554 --> 41:32.554
<i>♪♪</i>

41:34.203 --> 41:40.208
<i>MAN: ♪ Life can be
short, yes, it's true ♪</i>

41:40.209 --> 41:44.403
<i>♪ But don't let that get to you ♪</i>

41:44.404 --> 41:45.570
Hey.

41:45.571 --> 41:47.548
<i>♪♪</i>

41:47.549 --> 41:50.534
I thought you were
taking the later train.

41:50.535 --> 41:52.244
TIM: I was so anxious to get home.

41:52.245 --> 41:53.629
You scared me. (CHUCKLES)

41:53.630 --> 41:55.706
<i>♪♪</i>

41:55.707 --> 41:57.225
Ooh, what is this?

41:57.226 --> 41:58.917
It's from my mother.

41:58.918 --> 42:00.561
(SCOFFS)

42:00.562 --> 42:03.064
I'm not even pregnant and
she already knows it's a boy.

42:03.065 --> 42:05.007
But wait.

42:05.008 --> 42:08.236
There's actually one
from Spelman in there too.

42:08.237 --> 42:10.554
Okay, then.

42:10.555 --> 42:12.073
Issues.

42:12.074 --> 42:13.432
(LAUGHS)

42:13.433 --> 42:14.909
Your family always does the most.

42:14.910 --> 42:18.061
I know you weren't in
the office all weekend.

42:18.062 --> 42:20.748
Where were you when I called you?

42:20.749 --> 42:23.768
Okay, I'll... I'll be honest.

42:23.769 --> 42:25.235
Please.

42:25.236 --> 42:28.756
(INHALES AND EXHALES DEEPLY)

42:28.757 --> 42:30.925
The baby pressure's a lot,

42:30.926 --> 42:32.760
and I didn't know how to tell you,

42:32.761 --> 42:37.172
so I... you know, I went
to blow off some steam

42:37.173 --> 42:39.249
with some friends from law school.

42:39.250 --> 42:40.292
Which friends?

42:40.293 --> 42:42.586
(CHUCKLES)

42:42.587 --> 42:45.589
What, are you cross-examining me now?

42:45.590 --> 42:46.849
Do I have to?

42:46.850 --> 42:51.112
<i>♪♪</i>

